The Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) party is keen to welcome back members who  defected as part of its plans to strengthen it national chairman John Mbadi has said. Mbadi said the party wants to forge ahead united as it gears up for the future elections. He directed the party officials at the grassroots to avoid enforcing stringent rules that could create obstacle to the members who have shown interest of rejoining. “The party officials should not be a stumbling block to the people who are willing to rejoin the party. We want to focus on how to strengthen the party at the grassroots,” he said. Speaking in Ndhiwa sub-county, Homa Bay county on Saturday, Mbadi expressed concern that ODM has been experiencing reduced number of representatives at the National Assembly.